	<li id="comment-83433">
		<img alt='' src='http://i0.wp.com/pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/3451362034/442e7fe48d8e00bb590c0480d271c0ea_normal.jpeg?resize=44%2C44' class='avatar avatar-44' height='44' width='44' />		<p>
			<p>Very good summary, given that it took only 2 hours.<br />
Exchanges don&#8217;t regulate because exchanges make money out of volume. The way to regulate is simple. First HFT should not have information on the order book. Second, all trades can enter a very short &#8220;time zone&#8221; in which they are randomised in such a way that the flow is not disturbed.<br />
The third way is to create an exchange only for HFT. Let them fight it out as grown ups. Stealing candies from babies is not really ethical.<br />
No one can really know the impact of HFT on price formation. Excessive leverage in any system creates unknown risks.</p>
