	<li id="comment-83417">
		<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/01b8aad10323f3a55484e05d2adf7d67?s=44&#038;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D44' class='avatar avatar-44' height='44' width='44' />		<p>
			<p>About optimized regulatory checking.</p>
<p>If an automated system performs regulatory checks by itself, the system should have a separated account with its own trading capital, and probably a separate firm id. Absent these independence, HTF has no legal way to optimize regulatory checks better than firm wide regulatory checks. Obtaining these independence cost a significant trading capital. I don&#8217;t think that most HFTs are that profitable to justify the trading capital.</p>
<div class="pd-rating" id="pd_rating_holder_1431624_comm_83417"></div>		</p>
		<p>
