	<li id="comment-83416">
		<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/01b8aad10323f3a55484e05d2adf7d67?s=44&#038;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D44' class='avatar avatar-44' height='44' width='44' />		<p>
			<p>For the order internalization. Client orders may be internally matched against SIP feed abiding by all the regulations except one. For a buy order, if the actual market is down and the SIP feed is stale, the order processor can just match the order (sell), and buy back from the market.</p>
<p>As this is a riskless principal trade, the execution should be marked as such and the client should be informed. I am not sure that those executions are marked properly.</p>
<div class="pd-rating" id="pd_rating_holder_1431624_comm_83416"></div>		</p>
