	<li id="comment-83411">
		<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/01b8aad10323f3a55484e05d2adf7d67?s=44&#038;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D44' class='avatar avatar-44' height='44' width='44' />		<p>
			<p>Let&#8217;s say I sent an order of 10K (~$300K) MSFT. The internal matching engine of my broker (or the broker&#8217;s order processing firm) will probably just reroute the order to an exchange and send an prop order of 2K MSFT back to back to the same exchange. Which order do you think will arrive at the exchange first?</p>
<p>Just before a client order being routed to an exchange, the order should go through many regulatory checks and the order information should be checked in to a database system (Oracle). HFT&#8217;s order are being sent out without any checks. </p>
<p>Retail orders can be front-run in reality though the matching engine itself did not front-run retail orders.</p>
<div class="pd-rating" id="pd_rating_holder_1431624_comm_83411"></div>		</p>
