	<li id="comment-83331">
		<img alt='' src='http://i2.wp.com/graph.facebook.com/1571820644/picture?q=type%3Dlarge%26_md5%3D41ff0d2693738874bd9e58b0e176294d&#038;resize=44%2C44' class='avatar avatar-44' height='44' width='44' />		<p>
			<p>Douglas, the short answer is that Exchanges are making more money allowing the HFT&#8217;s to use their pipes.  In turn, the Brokers / Market Makers are being paid on trades to use certain exchanges instead of paying a flat rate or fee.  This has upended the dynamic the exchanges have historically created, the overall effect of which makes the market that much more ephemeral and opaque.  In my humble opinion, this short term view taken by Wall Street does not lend itself to the long term overall health of the markets, foreign or domestic.</p>
<div class="pd-rating" id="pd_rating_holder_1431624_comm_83331"></div>		</p>
		<p>
			<cite>
